Package: korean-ime-fixer
Version: 1.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Korean IME Community <maintainer@korean-ime.org>
Installed-Size: 15
Depends: fcitx5, fcitx5-hangul, im-config, systemd
Recommends: fcitx5-config-qt
Suggests: gnome-shell-extension-kimpanel
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/korean-ime/korean-ime-fixer
Description: Universal Korean IME fixer for Ubuntu systems
 This package automatically configures Fcitx5 input method framework
 to provide stable Korean input experience across all desktop environments.
 .
 Features:
  * Automatic environment detection (GNOME/KDE/XFCE, Wayland/X11)
  * Proper environment variable configuration
  * systemd user session integration
  * Complete removal support
  * Resolves Korean character input issues in browsers and applications
 .
 This package is specifically designed for Ubuntu and its derivatives,
 with focus on GNOME desktop environment and Wayland sessions.
